                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">The handwriting is characterized by
                           thick, big, rounded and right-slowing letters. The quality of the script
                           appears irregular (cp., e.g., <locus target="#22r">22r</locus>, 25v, 101r).
                           It is not sure if more than one hand was involved in the
                           writing.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (brilliant vermillion; strong vermillion for the
                           name Za-Manfas Qǝddus on <locus target="#41vb">41vb</locus>)</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12832Albastros">Albāsṭros</persName> is
                        mentioned as the scribe in the colophon and in Additio 1.
                        <date>Early 19th
                           century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ሕ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡ </expan> (in Text I-7; e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#114va">114va</locus>, 114vb, 115ra)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ካ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይብል፡ ካህን፡ </expan> (in Text I-7; e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#114va">114va</locus>, 114vc, 115ra, 115rc,
                              115vb-c)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ዲ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡ </expan> (in Texts I-7 and
                              I-9; e.g., <locus target="#114vc">114vc</locus>, 115ra, 115rc, 115vb,
                              197rb)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይተረጕ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይተረጕም፡ </expan> (in Text I-8; e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#146vb">146vb</locus>, 147rb)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ኪ፡/ኪር፡</abbr> for <expan>ኪራላይሶን፡ </expan> (Text I-8; <locus target="#172rc">172rc</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ስቡሕኒ፡</abbr> for <expan>ስቡሕኒ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወልዑልኒ፡ ውእቱ፡ ለዓለም፡ </expan>
                              (in Text I-8; <locus from="187va" to="188ra">187va-188ra</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ወይ፡ እግ፡ ተ፡ ጸ፡/ወይ፡ እግ፡ ጸ፡</abbr> for <expan>ወይብሉ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ተሣሃለነ፡
                                 ጸልዩ፡ </expan> (in Text I-9; <locus from="204ra" to="205rc">204ra-205rc</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names. Names of the king and
                           commissioner.
 A few lines alternating with black lines in the
                           incipit page of Text I-1 and in the incipit page of the section for the
                           day hours of Friday (in Text I-8); headings and incipits of the texts,
                           their sections and subsections; titles of the Biblical books and other
                           works; names of Hebrew letters in Text I-8; directives for the ministers
                           in Texts I-7and I-9; initial words or letters in “Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt” (Text
                           I-8); the words: yǝbe, yǝtaragʷǝm and yǝbe matargʷǝm in Text I-8.
                           Elements of the punctuation signs, of Ethiopic numerals and of the text
                           dividers.
                           <note>- In some parts of the text, the rubrication is missing (s. the
                              punctuations), looking like it has not been completed: <locus from="98v" to="99r">98v-99r</locus>, <locus from="157v" to="162r">157v-162r</locus>.</note>
                        </seg>
          
                     
                     <seg type="script"> Some distinctive
                        features:</seg>
                     <seg type="script"> - the upper horizontal strokes of some
                        letters (e.g., መ ሠ በ) are slightly slanted to the
                        left;</seg>
                     <seg type="script"> - the letter መ, in the 1st and 2nd
                        orders, has the right loop which does not rest on the ruled
                        line;</seg>
                     <seg type="script"> - some letters have hairlines at the
                        top (e.g., ን, ጸ, ይ,
                        ገ);</seg>
                     <seg type="script"> - ፪ is with the loop at the bottom
                        open (e.g, <locus target="#18va">18va</locus>);</seg>
                     <seg type="script"> - ፮ is with the loop open, looking
                        like “compressed” (s. the sixth hour of the days: e.g., <locus target="#103va">103va</locus>,
                        162vc);</seg>
                     <seg type="script"> - x-cross with dashes is used several
                        times, especially at the end of a book title or heading of texts (e.g.,
                           <locus target="#98rb">98rb</locus>,
                        100ra).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#205r">f. 205rb-rc</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">Ownership note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘታቦተ፡ ቁስቋም፡ ወለአጸሐፌሁ፡
                              ኃጥእ፡ ወድኩም፡ አልባስጥሮስ፡...</q>
                           <note>This note, written in the main hand, says that the
                           book belongs to the tābot of Qusqʷam (most likely one of the tābots of
                           the church Māryām Makān); besides, it mentions, like in the colophon
                              (<locus target="#131rc">131rc</locus>), Albāsṭros as the name (?) of the scribe. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>Space for rubricated names left unfilled in the
                           supplication formulas: e.g., <locus target="#179vc">179vc</locus>, 204rc,
                           204va, 180rc.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>Corrections (words or letters) written
                           interlineally: <locus target="#17rc">17rc</locus>, 30va, 45vc, 59ra,
                              61rb, 69va, 182vb.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>Erasures: e.g., <locus target="#27rb">27rb</locus>, 148rb.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>Erasures marked with parallel lines:
                              e.g., <locus target="#55vc">55vc</locus>, 116vb.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>Corrections over
                              erasures: e.g., <locus target="#148rb">148rb</locus>, 156ra, 156rc.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc>On <locus target="#142r">142r</locus> and 203v, part of the text
                           continues outside the layout, in the upper and bottom margin, in a
                           compressed script.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                           <desc>Writing exercise (?) in the bottom margin of
                              <locus target="#168r">168r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e8">
                           <desc>Crude recent notes in pen
                           in the margins of <locus from="129v" to="130r">129v-130r</locus>,
                           134v.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e9">
                           <desc type="findingAid">On <locus target="#51ra">fol. 51ra</locus>, an
                              omitted passage from the text (i.e. ቅድመ፡ ወንገል፡), introducing the
                              reading from the Gospel of Luke for the first night hour of Tuesday,
                              is written in the bottom margin. </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e10">
                           <desc type="findingAid">Excerpts of hymns for the Good
                              Friday (?) written (mostly in black; also in red on <locus target="#173v">fol. 173v</locus>; some with a frame below) in the
                              upper margin of fols. 132r, 141v, 142v, 143r, 145r, 151v, 152r, 152v,
                              162v, 169v, 170r, 170v, 171r, 173v, 179r, 179v, 182v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
